  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Service Crew",
  "description": "<p><em>A Service Crew member in the food &amp; beverage or retail industry is a frontline staff member responsible for providing excellent customer service, taking orders, serving food and beverages, preparing bills, and maintaining a clean and welcoming environment. Key duties include greeting guests, taking orders, serving customers, handling payments, cleaning tables, and ensuring customer satisfaction.   </em></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities  </strong></u></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Customer Interaction: Greet guests upon arrival, assist with seating, and provide prompt and courteous service throughout their visit.  </p>\n<p>Order Management: Present menus, answer questions about food and beverage items, take orders accurately, and recommend menu items to customers.  </p>\n<p>Service Delivery: Serve food and drinks to customers and ensure orders are delivered efficiently and correctly.  </p>\n<p>Payment Processing: Prepare bills that itemise costs and sales tax, process payments, and handle cash or credit card transactions.  </p>\n<p>Cleanliness &amp; Maintenance: Keep dining areas, work stations, and restrooms clean, organised, and well-maintained.  Team Support: Collaborate with other team members to ensure smooth operations and efficient service.   </p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Key Skills &amp; Qualities </strong></u></p>\n<p>• Customer Service: A strong ability to provide friendly, efficient, and professional service to customers.</p>\n<p> • Communication: Good interpersonal and basic communication skills to interact effectively with customers and colleagues.  </p>\n<p>• Teamwork: The ability to work well with others to achieve common goals.  </p>\n<p>• Adaptability: The ability to work in a fast-paced environment and manage multiple tasks effectively.  </p>\n<p>• Positive Attitude: A cheerful, positive, and service-oriented demeanor. </p>\n<p> • Attention to Detail: Accuracy in taking orders, handling payments, and maintaining cleanliness.</p>",
